Description: A woman sleeping, seated on a step in front of a building, her chin on her left hand and resting her elbow in her other hand, in her lap, wearing a gown, shawl and scarf around her head; with an urn behind to right; after an etching by Parmigianino (Bartsch 10); late state of circa 1750, after dedication added. Chiaroscuro woodcut printed from two blocks in black and ochre
Producer name: Print made by: John Baptist Jackson
Bibliographic references: Kainen 1962 / John Baptist Jackson, 18thc. master of the color woodcut (5)
Associated names: Representation of: St Thais of Egypt (?)
Associated with: Society of Antiquaries of London
